<TITLE> Home software threat to spy planes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WASHINTON, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)--The US military says it has fixed a security loophole that may have allowed hackers to tap into spy planes with over-the-counter software. Spy planes like this Predator drone are part of the eyes and ears of the US military in Iraq. It's now emerged that over-the-counter software costing just 26 dollars could have given insurgents ready access to its output of real time war zone video. The Wall Street Journal newspaper reports Shia fighters in Iraq have been using the software to intercept video feeds from the spy planes. One such programme is Sky Grabber developed by Russian firm SkySoftware. The newspaper says the US military discovered the loophole last year. It emerged when an insurgent was captured with digital files of video feeds on his laptop. It's not yet clear whether US military operations have been compromised. US officials say the security loophole has been fi
